reviews.review: This is an action pack Star Wars. Unfortunately it suffers from the previous Star Wars and tries to correct some previous decisions. I truly enjoyed it but see some flaws here and there.

It was good in the beginning of the movie but getting into the middle and end of the movie it felt really rushed there was good parts of thru the movie but it just was the best Star Wars movie from the new Trilogy like the prequel was better then this new trilogy if you see the trailers of this movie you pretty much know the whole movie just this was worst one for the Star Wars movies

I know that this movie try so hard to fix the previus caos of "The Last Jedi" of Rian Johnson, and that is why i liked becouse we had answers. Another thing that i like is the final part of the movie, just Epic. I am talking as a normal person who buy a ticket to see a good movie becouse if I talk as a star wars fan, I can give it maybe 2 or 3 of 5 starts just for a lot of inconsistencies all over the story that J,J. Abrams is telling us.
all the action and the connections were great just the ending i didnt like

I give it a 4 because it is the best Star Wars from this current trilogy, however the movie spends way too much time trying to fix the issues of the first two movies that it felt restricted in the telling of it's own story. As a movie it was enjoyable, but I left unsatisfied as a fan.
Very satisfying ending. Loved strong female characters and imaginative sets and costumes. I did wonder how Rey's outfit stayed so white most of the time.
Ties up loose ends from force awakens and last jedi. somewhat predictable, but at the same time, keeps you wondering what is really next.
Very Good Finale.... to a 42 year old franchise.

This movie has so much depth. I need to see it multiple times to fully understand the storyline and that's not a bad thing, that's what keeps it alive! A great movie in my opinion is a satisfying character arc and an unpredictable storyline. This movie contains both plus more.
